Page_0: "No Passion Among Thieves: Chapter 3

...and woefully did the bridesmaid Honeymelon thrust herself heaving into the arms of Dexter, the kind-hearted but misunderstood thief and bandit. 'Oh how I shall give up my ways for thee,'' he did cry, forsaking all of the wealth and power his profession forced him to seek.

Twas not long after they embraced in that cold steel chamber, lined with the symbolic alabaster of a forgotten age, that they were discovered by Hector, the woe-begotten fiance from Honeymelon's past..."